  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>sausage meat </strong>(remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tagliatelle</strong> for an initial 3-4 min, or until cooked with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is starting to brown, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and most of your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> soft cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce thickens slightly and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once your tagliatelle is ready, add the<strong> spinach </strong>to the pot and cook for a further 15 secs or until wilted, then once done, drain, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> tagliatelle </strong>and <strong>spinach </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) to the sauce and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is well coated – this is your <strong>spicy sausage & creamy tomato sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy sausage & creamy tomato sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
